name: TOTP2
overview: Fast-moving music show mixing classic performances from the Top of the Pops archives with exclusive live performances.

seasons.overview: For 2002, starting on 26th February, TOTP2 was shown twice a week on a Tuesday and Wednesday evening.

episodes.name: Robbie Williams Special
episodes.overview: Steve Wright presents a 'Space Odyssey' special featuring Robbie Williams.

episodes.name: John Lennon Special

episodes.name: February 26th, 2002
episodes.overview: Tonight's clips include performances by the Cure and Tina Turner, plus new music from Eva Cassidy and Nick Lowe. With the voice of Steve Wright.

episodes.name: February 27th, 2002
episodes.overview: As part of a preview of the Grammy Awards the archives throw up clips of some of the nominees, including Queen, U2, Janet Jackson and Shaggy.

episodes.name: March 5th, 2002
episodes.overview: Archive performances include Frank Sinatr , Tom Jones, Squeeze, Roxette and ABC.

episodes.name: March 6th, 2002
episodes.overview: Pop classics include Kate Bush, Opus 3, the Lambrettas, Andy Kim and No Doubt.

episodes.name: Rolling Stones Special
episodes.overview: Mick Jagger, Keith Richards, Charlie Watts and Ronnie Wood introduce their greatest hits during an exclusive interview for TOTP2 whilst on tour in New York.

episodes.overview: Frankie Goes to Hollywood, Cher, Communards, Razorlight, Sting, the Beach Boys, Chris Isaak , the Skids, Jamelia, Fox, Duran Duran ,  Human League, George Harrison and Nelly Furtado star in a special double-length episode to mark the show's return.

episodes.name: October 7, 2006
episodes.overview: Bananarama, Monty Python 's Eric Idle , Kylie, Jamelia and Richard Hawley are among the stars.

episodes.name: October 14, 2006
episodes.overview: Archive footage of New Order, Deacon Blue, Roy Orbison, the Bangles, Cliff Richard and TLC. Plus new performances from Nerina Pallot and Seth Lakeman.

episodes.name: October 21, 2006
episodes.overview: Archive footage of Roxette, Bonnie Tyler , Meat Loaf, Brian and Michael, the Byrds and Cockney Rebel. Plus a brand new performance from Amy Winehouse and an Oasis video exclusive.

episodes.name: October 28, 2006
episodes.overview: Archive classics from the likes of the Jam,  Haysi Fantayzee , Def Leppard , Tasmin Archer , Tracey Ullman and Leo Sayer. Plus a new performance from Vincent Vincent and the Villains.

episodes.name: November 4, 2006
episodes.overview: Archive classics from Culture Club, Moby, Tight Fit, 10cc, Madness, the Charlatans and the Tourists. Plus exclusives from All Saints and Gnarls Barkley.

episodes.name: November 11, 2006
episodes.overview: Includes new music by Jamiroquai and Ray LaMontagne.

episodes.name: November 18, 2006
episodes.overview: Archive classics featuring U2, Blondie, the KLF with Tammy Wynette, Stray Cats, Sinitta, Crowded House and Alvin Stardust. Plus new performances from Sandi Thorn and Kasabian.

episodes.name: November 25, 2006
episodes.overview: A selection of performances from yesteryear plus new sounds from today's hit makers.

episodes.name: December 2, 2006
episodes.overview: Archive hits by Ozzy Osbourne , Adam Ant. the Carpenters, Britney Spears and Take That. Plus new performances by the Fratellis and Nelly Furtado.

episodes.name: December 9, 2006
episodes.overview: Archive hits by Europe, the Buzzcocks, Vanessa Paradis and the Osmonds. Plus new music by Lil' Chris and Lily Allen.

episodes.name: December 16, 2006
episodes.overview: Archive hits from Bucks Fizz, Belinda Carlisle , Beats International, Linx and Christina Aguilera.  Plus a new performance from Razorlight.

episodes.name: Christmas Special (2006)
episodes.overview: A rundown of the greatest Christmas hits from the archive, introduced by Steve Wright.
